The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      BRIEFS
                  
	Bolpur, Dec. 16: A Birbhum court today directed the Government Railway Police and the Burdwan Medical College and Hospital to hand over the body of one of the passengers killed in the Sainthia accident in July.     
	Gangajali Sau of Bhojpur was forced to seek court help after hospital authorities refused to release her husband Bholas body despite furnishing papers.        
	Calcutta: Jharkhand Mukti Morcha Rajya Sabha member K.D. Singh has joined the Trinamul Congress. His entry raises the number of Trinamul members in the Upper House to three.        
	Durgapur: Relatives of a patient who died at a private hospital in Durgapur allegedly thrashed a doctor and women staff and destroyed hospital property, accusing them of handing over the body for post-mortem without informing them.         
	Calcutta: The state government will provide bicycles free to tribal girls of Classes IX-XII in Jungle Mahal from Monday, a senior official said.                                                                                                                                                      
